																		Author Post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227332" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1555093008 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Apr 2019 18:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4217164">
									

<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Excerpts</strong></p>
<hr />
<p><em>&quot;Right, because we can't just assassinate him in broad daylight.&quot; &quot;What? That's easy.&quot;</em></p>
<hr />
<p><em>A lance of pure force traveled down her arm and out her hand as she punched the Nazi wizard in the face with all the power of a speeding locomotive.</em></p>
<hr />
<p><em>The park was filled with a hellish honking as a flock of Canadian geese materialized in midair, confused and angry about being in Canada.</em></p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>The north wind rises, old man's eyes wondering deeply as he locks his door<br />
He knows the fear when I'm too near him, he's seen me angry before<br />
The black intruding clouds approach as I release a destructive blow<br />
All the crashing, all the flashing light brings terror upon my foe<br />
I fight with force and power for my land<br />
I command the lightning's hand!</em></p>
<p><span style="margin-left: 50%">Kansas &#8212; &quot;<a href="https://youtu.be/Z3hgCZQMk_w">Lightning's Hand</a>&quot;</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Part 4 is here, with apologies to the innocent citizens of Ontario. Regrettably, no Canadian geese were harmed in the writing of this tale. The Hub will be going up next Monday, and Part 5 will likely be on Wednesday after that.</p>
<p>Thanks to the following people for crit:</p>
<ul>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tawny0" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2244665); return false;">tawny0</a></span></li>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;">Jacob Conwell</a></span> &#8212; <a href="/the-time-we-had">The Time We Had</a></li>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;">TyGently</a></span> &#8212; <a href="/scp-4844">SCP-4844</a></li>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/9volt" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2800867); return false;">9Volt</a></span> &#8212; <a href="/barrels-of-prose">Barrels of Prose and Slugs of Pulp</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Extra special thanks to <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/crashington" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5028224); return false;">Crashington</a></span> for the art for this tale; check out their art page <a href="/crash-s-flashy-art-dash">here</a>. As a work done on commission for this tale, it automatically falls under CC-BY-SA 3.0.</p>
<p>Here's an alt version of the Ultimate Nazi Punch with some coloring to indicate magical energy: <a href="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/thunders-fist-solomons-hand/1fullflame.png">Link</a></p>
<p>This is the high point for Florence, as saving the world from Nazi wizards tends to be. From here on out, things are only going to get worse for our intrepid protagonist. The next arc of this series is going to be a collection of vignettes detailing her life at Site 246, and just how crappy it gets.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;A&nbsp;Note&nbsp;on&nbsp;Nazi&nbsp;Punching</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Punching&nbsp;Nazis&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;Moral&nbsp;Imperative</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>When writing <a href="/obskuracorps-memos">Obskuracorps Memos</a>, I tried to portray the evil of the Nazi regime with as much realism and accuracy as is possible for an urban fantasy setting. It was an exercise in trying to understand, or at least realize, the motives of human monsters, and writing it required putting myself into a truly upsetting headspace.</p>
<p>This is my answer to that. There is no attempt to humanize the villains here. They are Nazis and they are evil, and the only proper thing to do is punch them in the face with lethal force. If you have a problem with that, I suggest you do something anatomically impossible.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

